methods.name: getCacheDir
methods.notes:
Returns the root cache folder. Used for all save/settings/etc. files in the user directory.
  The returned folder exists on arrival.

methods.name: getCacheDirSub
methods.notes:
Returns the subPath, relative to the CacheDir path.
  NOTE: Does not create the subPath, nor ensure that it exists.

methods.name: getMessagingDir
methods.notes:
Returns the messaging folder. Used for writing Trigger files for communicating with the game.
  The returned folder exists on arrival.

methods.name: getMessagingDirSub
methods.notes:
Returns the messaging folder. Used for writing Trigger files for communicating with the game.
  NOTE: Does not create the subPath, nor ensure that it exists.

methods.name: getSaveDirSub
methods.notes:
Returns the subPath, relative to the SaveDir path.
  NOTE: Does not create the subPath, nor ensure that it exists.

methods.name: getScreenshotDirSub
methods.notes:
Returns the subPath, relative to the ScreenshotDir path.
  NOTE: Does not create the subPath, nor ensure that it exists.

methods.name: resolveFileOrGUID
methods.notes:
Takes a string source, which is either a GUID or a file path. Returns a file
 path, if found. If none is found, returns the original source.

methods.name: setCacheDir
methods.notes:
Specify root cache folder. Used for all save/settings/etc. files in the user directory.
  If the specified folder does not exist, is created on the spot.
